data.title: Good food, unique and frequently very busy
data.text:
Living in the area, we enjoy down town Gilbert.  Liberty Market is a nice place to eat.  The menu is very good, food fresh and the atmosphere is normally bustling.

There's a line that you order and your food is brought to you. Due to the popularity of Liberty Market, the lines can get to be very long and there can be very few places to sit which gets to be frustrating.  

Keep this in mind if you are coming with children because larger tables are few.

To really get and enjoy the Liberty Market menu I would suggest breakfast or coming a little early for lunch or dinner.

Plenty of vegan or vegetarian options.  Frequently, if you don't see what you would like or would like to modify a meal they are generally very happy to do so.

data.title: A Unique Breakfast
data.text: The menu is eclectic and creative.  Just enough creativity to peak your interest but so crazy that it will scare your kids!  My son and I love the place and have had several great breakfasts here!  Highly recommended!

data.title: Liberty Market
data.text: We arrived about 7 pm on Thursday and it was busy but not 100 % full. Many options here for any meal period. Appears to be comfort type food for the most part and many items are prepared as you order, however you place your order and sit at the table of your choice without being able to see the open kitchen actually preparing your product. The kitchen line had some cleanliness issues as i walked down the viewing area. We ordered the fresh fish and the chicken with sweet potatoes and looked appealing when served but didn't sit well later.

data.title: Liberty Market
data.text: Love this place have eaten here for breakfast, lunch and dinner and always had excellent food and service. If you want to go in for a specialty coffee this is a good choice.  You can dine in or now that the temperatures have gone down the outdoor patio is an excellent option.

owner_response.author: Sarah R, Social Media Manager at Liberty Market, responded to this review
owner_response.text: Thanks so much for coming in, and coming back. We appreciate it very much.
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Morning, Noon and Night Yumminess!
data.text:
I've been here for all the above and have yet get a bad meal. Had different types of foods from munchies, salads,
full meals, even desserts and its ALL been delicious! They also have cocktails to have with your meals too! You will NOT be disappointed.

owner_response.author: Sarah R, Social Media Manager at Liberty Market, responded to this review
owner_response.text: Thanks for coming in! We're glad you enjoyed EVERYTHING.
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Casual eatery
data.text:
The place is very casual outside sitting the food is excellent especially the sconces with whipped cream on the side.
I personally love to go at breakfast, but their lunch and dinner is also very good.
You cannot go wrong going anytime. 
One thing to know you need to go to the counter to order PS the food is really good and the staff is very helpful.

data.title: Great preserved space!
data.text: Really liked this spot in downtown. One of the older spaces revitalized to a creative casual restaurant. Good specials that change daily. Excellent salads and sandwiches.  Good desserts too!

data.title: Near Ideal Evening
data.text: Want something casual, fun, yet truly yum food?  That would be Liberty Market. The atmosphere is friendly and upbeat. They offer both indoor and outdoor seating, your choice. And did I mention that the food was yum? Appropriate for birthday, anniversary, before event dining, w/ or w/o friends. Very satisfying.

owner_response.author: Sarah R, Social Media Manager at Liberty Market, responded to this review
owner_response.text: We are so glad you enjoyed your evening and look forward to seeing you again soon.
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Loved the carrot cake!
data.text: We came in here after eating somewhere else nearby, and walked out with a piece of carrot cake.  It was delicious and coated in toasted coconut.  Service was friendly and all the food we saw coming out of the kitchen looked really good.  We can't wait to come back and try some real food!

owner_response.author: Sarah R, Social Media Manager at Liberty Market, responded to this review
owner_response.text: I LOVE our carrot cake. Can't wait to see you when you come back. Thanks for coming for dessert.
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Just ok
data.text: We came in on a Saturday night the wait was long but that expected in this area. We had the Margarita Pizza and Apricot Glazed Chicken. The pizza was good; not great but not bad. The chicken was dry, the potatoes tasted like whip potatoes but no real seasoning. The best with was the glaze. It was yummy. Not sure we would come back again.

owner_response.author: Sarah R, Social Media Manageer at Liberty Market, responded to this review
owner_response.text: Thanks for coming in. Sorry to hear you did not enjoy everything. If there's something specific you think we could work on, please let us know.
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Killer Coffee
data.text: Liberty Market is a great place for breakfast, especially if you are out for a relaxing Sunday breakfast with your significant other. One of the best things about LB is that they serve what's called a Cortadino. It's a kind of coffee from Cuba or Colombia. Either way it is like rocket fuel!! 😀

owner_response.author: Sarah R, Social Media Manager at Liberty Market, responded to this review
owner_response.text: Thank you very much for having breakfast with us. Our Cortaditos are my weak spot!
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Excellent Breakfast!
data.text: Came here for the first time for breakfast and really enjoyed The Italian Scramble, The Chai Latte. Very filling and satisfied,  The owner was present and suggested in our next dinning to have other things on the menu.

owner_response.author: Sarah R, Social Media Manager at Liberty Market, responded to this review

data.title: A Liberating Lunch
data.text: This restaurant was recommended by friends so we all got together for lunch.  It reminded me of the cafeteria lunch line in school for ordering but the food was over the top great.  Our table ordered differently so we could get a wider variety of tastes.  It was really good.  Staff and service was polite and friendly and made you feel welcome.  Highly recommend Liberty Market.

data.title: In for a snack
data.text: Stopped at Liberty Square for coffee and their fabulous cinnamon roll, which are even better than Cinnabon's.  Learned how good they were when they offered a free cinnamon tool to veterans on Memorial Day.

data.title: Fun, historic building, decent food.

data.title: Excellent and healthy--until I ate the blueberry scone!
data.text: Queso chorizo dip was a delicious starter. I had the chopped salad. I loved the bits of pumpkin seed brittle and the dried apricots. Dressing was light and everything was crisp that was meant to be. I hate an overdressed, soggy salad. Finished the meal with a blueberry scone. Just sweet enough with the perfect texture.

owner_response.author: Sarah R, Social Media Manager at Liberty Market, responded to this review

owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Met a friend at this place for lunch.
data.text: I met a friend for lunch at Liberty Market.  The food was outstanding.  I just felt that it was so crowded (probably because of the awesome food).  I also prefer not to stand in line for my food.  However, the manager made sure we could find a table after getting our food.

owner_response.author: Sarah R, Social Media Manager at Liberty Market, responded to this review
